deriv:{title:'Derivatives',eye:'Tested ALL 3 Levels &#8212; weight grows L1&#8594;L2&#8594;L3',weights:{l1:'5&#8211;8%',l2:'5&#8211;10%',l3:'10&#8211;15%'},
  overview:'The only non-ethics topic tested at all three levels with growing weight. L1: payoffs and no-arbitrage basics. L2: Black-Scholes model, Greeks, swap valuation. L3: applying derivatives to manage portfolio risk &#8212; beta/duration/currency adjustment and options strategies.',
  notes:[
    {title:'Forwards, Futures & Swaps (L1/L2)',lv:['l1','l2'],sum:'Basic derivative instruments. No-arbitrage pricing, hedging applications, and swap valuation.',
      kcs:[
        {title:'Forward & Futures Pricing',lv:['l1','l2'],col:'#E67E22',lead:'No-arbitrage pricing: F = S&#8320; &#215; (1+r)^T &#8722; FV(income). Daily mark-to-market for futures.',
          notes:[{t:'Pricing by Asset Class',b:'Equity forward: F = (S &#8722; PV(Div)) &#215; (1+r)^T. Currency forward: F = S &#215; (1+r_d)/(1+r_f)^T (covered IRP). Commodity: F = S &#215; e^((r+u&#8722;y)T) where u=storage, y=convenience yield.'},{t:'Hedging',b:'Short hedge: sell forward &#8594; lock in selling price. Long hedge: buy forward &#8594; lock in purchase price. At expiry: forward price converges to spot price.'}]},
        {title:'Swaps',lv:['l1','l2'],col:'#2980B9',lead:'Interest rate, currency, and equity swaps. Swap = series of forward contracts.',
          notes:[{t:'IRS Valuation',b:'Interest rate swap value = PV(fixed payments to receive) &#8722; PV(floating payments to make). Fixed rate = rate that sets swap value to zero at initiation. Receive-fixed swap = long bond + short floating rate note.'},{t:'Currency Swaps',b:'Exchange principal AND interest in two currencies. Used by multinationals to match currency of assets and liabilities. More complex than IRS &#8212; involves exchange of notional at start and end.'}]},
      ]
    },
    {title:'Options (L1/L2)',lv:['l1','l2'],sum:'Option payoffs, put-call parity, Black-Scholes model, and option Greeks.',
      kcs:[
        {title:'Option Payoffs & Strategies',lv:['l1'],col:'#27AE60',lead:'Long call: max(S&#8722;K,0). Long put: max(K&#8722;S,0). Put-call parity: C &#8722; P = S &#8722; PV(K).',
          notes:[{t:'Put-Call Parity',b:'C &#8722; P = S &#8722; PV(K). Links call, put, stock, and bond. Violation = arbitrage. Rearrange to price any one from the other three.'},{t:'Basic Strategies',b:'Covered call: long stock + short call = income generation, caps upside. Protective put: long stock + long put = insurance, limits downside. Collar = both combined &#8594; bounded payoff. Straddle: long call + long put at same K = profit from large move either direction.'}]},
        {title:'Black-Scholes & Greeks (L2)',lv:['l2'],col:'#C0392B',lead:'C = S&#215;N(d&#8321;) &#8722; K&#215;e^(&#8722;rT)&#215;N(d&#8322;). Five Greeks: Delta, Gamma, Theta, Vega, Rho.',
          notes:[{t:'Black-Scholes',b:'d&#8321; = [ln(S/K) + (r+&#963;&#178;/2)T] / (&#963;&#8730;T). d&#8322; = d&#8321; &#8722; &#963;&#8730;T. Assumes: log-normal prices, constant volatility, European exercise, no dividends. Implied vol: back-solve for &#963; given observed market price.'},{t:'The Greeks',b:'Delta = N(d&#8321;) for calls: sensitivity to stock price. Gamma: rate of change of delta. Theta: time decay (negative for long options). Vega: sensitivity to volatility. Rho: sensitivity to interest rate.'},{t:'Vol Skew',b:'Implied vol varies by strike &#8212; puts have higher implied vol (crash insurance demand). Violates Black-Scholes constant-vol assumption. Indicates fat-tail risk premium priced into options.'}]},
      ]
    },
    {title:'Portfolio Derivatives (L3)',lv:['l3'],sum:'Using derivatives as portfolio management tools to adjust equity beta, fixed income duration, currency exposure, and volatility.',
      kcs:[
        {title:'Beta & Duration Adjustment',lv:['l3'],col:'#27AE60',lead:'Use futures to adjust portfolio beta (equity) or duration (fixed income) quickly and cheaply.',
          notes:[{t:'Beta Formula',b:'N_futures = (&#946;_target &#8722; &#946;_portfolio) / &#946;_futures &#215; (Portfolio Value / Futures Contract Value). Positive = BUY futures (increase beta). Negative = SELL (reduce). Much cheaper than trading underlying stocks.'},{t:'Duration Formula',b:'N = (D_target &#8722; D_current) &#215; Portfolio Value / (D_futures &#215; Futures Price). Positive = BUY bond futures (extend duration). Used in pension fund LDI implementation.'},{t:'Why Futures Not Stocks',b:'Futures: (1) lower transaction costs, (2) faster execution, (3) no disruption to existing portfolio, (4) tax-efficient. Ideal for tactical allocation changes, temporary hedges, and liability management.'}]},
        {title:'Currency Management',lv:['l3'],col:'#E67E22',lead:'Forward contracts to hedge FX exposure. Dynamic hedging. Currency overlay. Cross-hedging.',
          notes:[{t:'Hedge Decision',b:'Full hedge: eliminates FX risk, locks in forward rate. Partial hedge: reduces FX risk, maintains some currency exposure. No hedge: accept full currency risk. Decision depends on view and correlation between currency and underlying asset.'},{t:'Roll Yield',b:'Hedging cost = interest rate differential (covered IRP). If domestic rates > foreign, forward > spot &#8594; hedging foreign assets is costly. If domestic < foreign &#8594; hedging generates positive roll yield.'}]},
        {title:'Options Portfolio Strategies',lv:['l3'],col:'#8E44AD',lead:'Protective put, covered call, collar, straddle, strangle for portfolio risk management.',
          notes:[{t:'Core Applications',b:'Protective put: long put on portfolio &#8594; downside floor, preserves upside. Covered call: short call on portfolio &#8594; income in flat/rising market, caps upside above strike. Collar: protective put + covered call &#8594; bounded range, near-zero cost if strikes chosen carefully.'},{t:'Straddle & Strangle',b:'Long straddle: long call + long put at same strike &#8594; profit from large move either direction. Long strangle: OTM call + OTM put &#8594; cheaper than straddle but needs larger move to profit. Sell these to earn premium when expecting low volatility.'}]},
      ]
    },
  ],
  outcomes:{objective:'Price, value, and apply derivative instruments to manage equity, fixed income, currency, and volatility risk at the portfolio level.',
    byLevel:{
      l1:['Calculate forward and futures prices using no-arbitrage relationships','Compute option payoffs and draw profit diagrams for basic strategies','Verify put-call parity and identify arbitrage violations','Explain how swaps decompose into forward contracts'],
      l2:['Apply Black-Scholes to price European options','Calculate and interpret all five option Greeks','Value interest rate, currency, and equity swaps','Use binomial trees to price options including American early exercise'],
      l3:['Calculate futures needed to adjust portfolio beta or duration','Design covered call, protective put, and collar strategies','Construct currency hedging programmes using forwards','Apply rate swaps, caps, and floors for liability management']},
    skills:['Option Pricing','Greeks','Futures Overlay','Currency Hedging','Portfolio Risk Management']},
  resources:[
    {type:'yt',t:'Derivatives Complete Review &#8212; L1',ch:'IFT (Arif Irfanullah)',tags:['free','l1'],url:'https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=CFA+derivatives+IFT+level+1+complete'},
    {type:'yt',t:'Black-Scholes & Greeks Explained',ch:'The Plain Bagel',tags:['free','l2'],url:'https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=black+scholes+greeks+explained+simply'},
    {type:'yt',t:'Derivatives for Portfolio Management &#8212; L3',ch:'Mark Meldrum',tags:['free','l3'],url:'https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=CFA+level+3+derivatives+portfolio+management+mark+meldrum'},
    {type:'yt',t:'Options Strategies Visualised',ch:'tastytrade',tags:['free','l2','l3'],url:'https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=options+strategies+tastytrade+explained'},
