pm_p:{title:'L3 Pathway: Portfolio Management',eye:'Level 3 Specialised Pathway &#183; 30&#8211;35% of exam',weights:{l1:'&#8212;',l2:'&#8212;',l3:'30&#8211;35%'},
  overview:'For institutional asset managers. Covers managing assets for DB pension funds, endowments, sovereign wealth funds, and insurance companies. Advanced multi-asset strategies, LDI, and institutional due diligence.',
  notes:[
    {title:'Institutional Client Types',lv:['l3'],sum:'Each institutional client type has distinct liability characteristics, time horizons, liquidity needs, tax status, and regulatory constraints.',
      kcs:[
        {title:'DB Pension Funds',lv:['l3'],col:'#2980B9',lead:'Liability = PV of future benefit payments. Surplus = Assets &#8722; Liabilities. LDI to protect surplus.',
          notes:[{t:'LDI Implementation',b:'Hedging portfolio: matches liability duration and inflation sensitivity (long bonds + rate swaps + inflation swaps). Return-seeking portfolio: targets excess returns to grow surplus (equities, alternatives). The hedging portfolio protects; the return-seeking portfolio grows.'},{t:'Funded Ratio',b:'Funded ratio = Assets / PV(Liabilities). > 100% = overfunded (can take more risk). < 100% = underfunded (regulatory pressure to de-risk, may require employer contributions). Key metric for pension investment policy.'}]},
        {title:'Endowments & Foundations',lv:['l3'],col:'#27AE60',lead:'Perpetual time horizon. High illiquidity tolerance. Endowment model. Spending rule typically 4&#8211;5%.',
          notes:[{t:'Endowment Model',b:'Yale model (David Swensen): heavy alternatives (PE, hedge funds, real assets), minimal fixed income, selective equities. Works for perpetual institutions with long horizons. Fails for entities with near-term cash needs.'},{t:'Return Objective',b:'Return objective = spending rate + inflation + management fees. Typically 7&#8211;8% nominal to preserve purchasing power. Must earn above this rate to grow real assets in perpetuity.'}]},
        {title:'Insurance & Sovereign Wealth',lv:['l3'],col:'#C0392B',lead:'Insurance: conservative, regulation-driven, ALM-focused. SWFs: large, long-horizon, political constraints.',
          notes:[{t:'Insurance',b:'Life insurance: long-duration liabilities &#8594; match with long bonds. P&C: short-tail (auto) vs long-tail (liability) claims &#8594; different asset durations needed. RBC (risk-based capital) regulatory requirements constrain allocation. ALM is primary objective.'},{t:'Sovereign Wealth Funds',b:'Types: stabilisation (commodity revenues), savings (intergenerational), reserve investment, development, pension reserve. Long time horizons, large AUM, low liquidity needs. Must separate political influence from investment decision-making.'}]},
      ]
    },
  ],
